  "slug": "as-of-july-2026-financial-and-bankruptcy-status-of-6c2b2dbf",
  "query": "As of July 2026, financial and bankruptcy status of these companies: Chegg Inc, America's Car-Mart Inc, JetBlue Airways, Peloton Inc, Faraday Future Intelligent Electric, Petco Health and Wellness. Which are at highest risk of bankruptcy filing in mid-2026? Any going concern warnings, debt maturities, or restructuring news?",
  "answer": "I've completed the research. Here's the summary of findings on the six companies as of July 2026:\n\n## Bankruptcy Risk Ranking (Highest \u2192 Lowest)\n\n**1. America's Car-Mart (CRMT) \u2014 HIGHEST/IMMINENT RISK**\n- Actively exploring Chapter 11; advisor Houlihan Lokey seeking \u2265$500M new capital to avert bankruptcy\n- Under lender forbearance for actual/anticipated defaults; \"Specified Period\" runs to Sept 7, 2026\n- Q3 FY2026 net loss \u2013$76.7M; ~$892M total debt; stock down ~94% from 52-week high\n\n**2. Faraday Future (FFAI, formerly FFIE) \u2014 CRITICAL**\n- Explicit going-concern warning; management says it will \"likely seek bankruptcy protection\" without new funding\n- Q1 2026: only $512k revenue, \u2013$42.3M loss, ~$12.2M cash, ~$4.74B accumulated deficit\n- (Ticker changed from FFIE to FFAI \u2014 no data returns under FFIE anymore)\n\n**3. Chegg (CHGG) \u2014 ELEVATED but more manageable**\n- NYSE delisting risk (sub-$1 stock), planning reverse split; revenue down ~48% YoY from AI disruption\n- BUT largely defused its $1.0B 2026 convertible notes via buybacks (~$33.9M left) \u2014 near-term debt-wall risk low\n\n**4. JetBlue (JBLU) \u2014 MODERATE (deep speculative grade)**\n- Q1 2026 net loss \u2013$319M; rated CCC+ (Fitch)/B-/B3; ~$755M debt due 2026\n- BUT ~$2.4B liquidity and no going-concern warning \u2014 not imminent\n\n**5. Petco (WOOF) \u2014 LOW** \u2014 just refinanced $1.5B (maturities to 2031), deleveraged to 3.0x, returned to profit\n\n**6. Peloton (PTON) \u2014 LOW** \u2014 returned to profitability, positive EBITDA\n\n**Bottom line:** Two names carry near-imminent bankruptcy risk in mid-2026: **America's Car-Mart** (active Chapter 11 exploration + defaults) and **Faraday Future** (explicit going-concern, near-empty treasury). The full structured findings with all data points and sources have been recorded.",
